History: -year-old female with hyperglycemia. Evaluation for pneumonia.
Findings: PA and lateral views of the chest demonstrate hyperexpansion of the lungs and relative flattening of the bilateral hemidiaphragms, consistent with emphysema. Multilevel degenerative changes are present in the thoracic spine. Bilateral nipple shadows should not be confused for pulmonary nodules.
